hopobject.body: How much is a Second Class stamp? hillside medical clinic victoria In the Chicago region alone, the Morton Arboretum said a 2010 count showed ash trees made up about 8 percent of the canopy, or about 12.7 million trees. That figure includes ash trees in private yards, not just parkways. Cash-strapped towns are trying to figure out how to come up with the dollars to remove the trees and plant new ones. Last month, Gov. Pat Quinn signed a bill that included a provision that would allow communities to borrow money, up to $5 million statewide, from the state for the effort.
